{%- comment -%}
  Vertex AI Recommendations — v2 production slot renderer.
  Replaces the old placeholder snippet (which leaked preview chrome to live).

  ── Placement routing ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Pass `placement:` to select the data source and layout class:

  | placement                | data source                                         |
  |--------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
  | pdp_below_atc            | product.metafields.vertex.recs                      |
  | pdp_below_description    | product.metafields.vertex.similar                   |
  | cart_above_checkout      | cart.items[0].vertex.cart_recs → .recs fallback     |
  | home_below_hero          | customer.vertex.recommended_for_you → shop.trending |
  | cart_drawer_below_items  | cart.items[0].vertex.recs (v1 fallback)             |

  ── Arguments ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    placement  {String}   — slot identifier (required; defaults to 'unknown')
    product    {Product}  — anchor product (PDP placements)
    cart       {Cart}     — cart object (cart placements)
    customer   {Customer} — customer object (home RFY logged-in path)
    title      {String}   — section heading (required for customer-facing copy)
    subtitle   {String}   — section subheading (optional)
    rationale  {String}   — dev note shown in theme editor only (never on live)

  ── Safety gates ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  · Empty-state: if rec_products resolves to 0 items, the entire <section>
    is suppressed — no "No products" message renders on live.
  · Preview chrome (VERTEX badge + placement label) only renders when
    request.design_mode is true (theme editor). Never on preview-themed
    shop URLs or live.

  ── Performance ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  · Zero new JS — CSS scroll-snap only.
  · Images: WebP <picture> + JPEG fallback, explicit width/height, lazy.
  · CSS: assets/vertex-recommendations.css (long-cached, ~8 KB).

  Phase 1b-γ.8 (2026-05-02): PR-1 universal foundation.
  See task-1-recommendations.md for PR sequencing + open questions.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  assign placement    = placement | default: 'unknown'
  assign rec_title    = title     | default: 'You might also like'
  assign rec_subtitle = subtitle  | default: ''

  assign rec_products = ''
  assign rec_source   = 'placeholder'

  case placement
    when 'pdp_below_atc'
      if product and product.metafields.vertex.recs
        assign rec_products = product.metafields.vertex.recs.value
        assign rec_source   = 'metafield'
      endif

    when 'pdp_below_description'
      if product and product.metafields.vertex.similar
        assign rec_products = product.metafields.vertex.similar.value
        assign rec_source   = 'metafield'
      endif

    when 'cart_above_checkout'
      if cart and cart.items.first
        if cart.items.first.product.metafields.vertex.cart_recs
          assign rec_products = cart.items.first.product.metafields.vertex.cart_recs.value
          assign rec_source   = 'metafield'
        elsif cart.items.first.product.metafields.vertex.recs
          assign rec_products = cart.items.first.product.metafields.vertex.recs.value
          assign rec_source   = 'metafield_fallback'
        endif
      endif

    when 'home_below_hero'
      if customer and customer.metafields.vertex.recommended_for_you
        assign rec_products = customer.metafields.vertex.recommended_for_you.value
        assign rec_source   = 'metafield'
      elsif shop.metafields.vertex.homepage_trending
        comment
          Precompute writes shop.metafields.vertex.homepage_trending (NOT
          .trending) — confirmed against precompute/main.py:206-214.
        endcomment
        assign rec_products = shop.metafields.vertex.homepage_trending.value
        assign rec_source   = 'trending'
      endif

    when 'cart_drawer_below_items'
      if cart and cart.items.first and cart.items.first.product.metafields.vertex.recs
        assign rec_products = cart.items.first.product.metafields.vertex.recs.value
        assign rec_source   = 'metafield'
      endif

    else
      if product and product.metafields.vertex.recs
        assign rec_products = product.metafields.vertex.recs.value
        assign rec_source   = 'metafield'
      endif
  endcase

  comment
    Fallback to sample products so the slot is visually populated in the
    preview/development theme before the precompute model goes ACTIVE.
    On live with an ACTIVE model, the metafield branch above always fires
    and this block is skipped.
  endcomment
  unless rec_products
    for col in collections
      if col.products.size >= 4
        assign rec_products = col.products | sample: 4
        break
      endif
    endfor
  endunless

  assign card_count = rec_products.size | default: 0
-%}

{%- comment -%}
  Pre-render the rail into a buffer so we can detect whether ANY card
  actually rendered (avoids "header-with-no-cards" when every metafield
  handle resolves to a deleted/unpublished product).

  Two iteration shapes:
  1. Sample-fallback path → rec_products is a list of Shopify Product
     objects (from `collections | sample: 4`). entry.url is set.
  2. Metafield path → rec_products is a parsed JSON array of dicts
     {id, handle, vendor, score, final_score, margin_pct} written by
     precompute (type: "json", not list.product_reference). entry.url
     is nil; we resolve via all_products[entry.handle].
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- capture rail_html -%}
  {%- for entry in rec_products limit: 8 -%}
    {%- if entry.url -%}
      {%- render 'vertex-rec-card', product: entry, placement: placement -%}
    {%- else -%}
      {%- assign resolved = all_products[entry.handle] -%}
      {%- if resolved and resolved.handle != blank -%}
        {%- render 'vertex-rec-card', product: resolved, placement: placement -%}
      {%- endif -%}
    {%- endif -%}
  {%- endfor -%}
{%- endcapture -%}

{%- comment -%}
  Empty-state gate: suppress the entire section if EITHER (a) no products
  in the source list, OR (b) every product failed to resolve. Both states
  are treated identically — render nothing.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign rail_trimmed = rail_html | strip -%}
{%- if card_count == 0 or rail_trimmed == '' -%}{%- else -%}

{%- comment -%}
  Show preview chrome + team-notes panel on any non-live theme:
    theme.role == 'main'         → live theme   → chrome OFF
    theme.role == 'unpublished'  → draft theme  → chrome ON
    theme.role == 'demo'         → demo theme   → chrome ON
  This also covers the Shopify theme editor (where request.design_mode
  is true and theme.role is 'unpublished'). Lets reviewers see VERTEX
  badges and decision notes via preview-themed shop URLs without an
  admin login.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign show_preview_chrome = false -%}
{%- if theme.role != 'main' -%}
  {%- assign show_preview_chrome = true -%}
{%- endif -%}

<section
  class="vrec-slot vrec-slot--{{ placement }}{% if show_preview_chrome %} vrec-slot--preview{% endif %}"
  data-vertex-placement="{{ placement }}"
  data-vertex-anchor="{% if product %}{{ product.id }}{% endif %}"
  data-vertex-product-id="{% if product %}{{ product.id }}{% endif %}"
  data-vertex-source="{{ rec_source }}"
  aria-labelledby="vrec-title-{{ placement }}"
>
  {%- if show_preview_chrome -%}
    <div class="vrec-slot__preview-chrome" aria-hidden="true">
      <span class="vertex-rec-slot__badge">VERTEX</span>
      <span class="vertex-rec-slot__placement-label">{{ placement | replace: '_', ' ' }}</span>
    </div>

    {%- comment -%}
      Plain-language team-decision notes per placement.
      Visible only on non-live themes; never on live (theme.role check).
      Goal: every decision the team needs to approve appears INLINE next
      to the slot it affects, so reviewing the draft theme is equivalent
      to reading a decision memo.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <aside class="vrec-slot__notes" data-vertex-notes>
      <header class="vrec-slot__notes-header">
        <span class="vrec-slot__notes-eyebrow">Team review · Decisions</span>
        <span class="vrec-slot__notes-source" title="Data source for this slot">
          source: <code>{{ rec_source }}</code>
        </span>
      </header>
      <ul class="vrec-slot__notes-list">
        {%- case placement -%}
          {%- when 'pdp_below_atc' -%}
            <li><strong>Look & feel:</strong> approve the new layout — centered serif title with hairline rule, scroll-snap rail (4 desktop / 2.25 mobile), no inline ADD button. Replaces the old grey "rationale" placeholder.</li>
            <li><strong>Title copy:</strong> &ldquo;Complete the routine&rdquo; — keep, or change to something like &ldquo;Pairs well with this&rdquo; / &ldquo;Often bought together&rdquo;?</li>
            <li><strong>Live status:</strong> this slot is the only one already live on every PDP today. PR-2 cleans up the placeholder.</li>
          {%- when 'cart_above_checkout' -%}
            <li><strong>Inline ADD button:</strong> v1 ships <em>without</em> the inline one-tap ADD — cards click through to the PDP instead. Adding inline ADD requires either a small JS init (~10 lines) or relocating the slot. Approve click-through for v1, OR approve the JS budget for v2 inline-ADD.</li>
            <li><strong>Title copy:</strong> &ldquo;Frequently bought with these items&rdquo; — keep?</li>
            <li><strong>Subtitle:</strong> &ldquo;Add to your cart in one tap.&rdquo; — drop this if v1 has no inline ADD (it would mislead).</li>
            <li><strong>Layout:</strong> 2 stacked horizontal cards (desktop) / 1.1-card scroll rail (mobile). Approve.</li>
          {%- when 'cart_drawer_below_items' -%}
            <li><strong>Drawer FBT:</strong> 2.25-card horizontal scroll rail, no inline ADD (drawer AJAX-rerender has known race conditions). Cards click through to the PDP. Approve.</li>
            <li><strong>Title copy:</strong> &ldquo;Add to your routine&rdquo; — fits HairMNL voice?</li>
            <li><strong>Future v2:</strong> if engineering confirms the drawer AJAX rerender is atomic, we could add a <code>+</code> button on each card. Flagged for later.</li>
          {%- when 'home_below_hero' -%}
            <li><strong>Wiring:</strong> the homepage already has the maximum 25 sections, so this slot is <em>not</em> auto-added to the homepage. When the RFY model goes ACTIVE (~May 7), an admin needs to add &ldquo;Vertex recommendations&rdquo; via the theme editor between the hero and category-pills strip.</li>
            <li><strong>Logged-in title:</strong> &ldquo;Trending in your routine&rdquo; — keep, or rename?</li>
            <li><strong>Anonymous title:</strong> &ldquo;Trending now&rdquo; — keep, or rename?</li>
            <li><strong>Subtitles:</strong> default empty. Approve, or set defaults like &ldquo;Picked for you, based on your history.&rdquo; / &ldquo;What HairMNL shoppers are loving this week.&rdquo;?</li>
          {%- when 'pdp_below_description' -%}
            <li><strong>Position:</strong> below the description tabs (recovery slot for users who scrolled past the ADD button without converting). Lower decorative weight than slot 1 — no hairline rule.</li>
            <li><strong>Title copy:</strong> &ldquo;You may also like&rdquo; — keep?</li>
            <li><strong>Conflict check:</strong> Pipeline 6.1.3&rsquo;s native &ldquo;You May Also Like&rdquo; section is NOT wired in <code>templates/product.json</code>, so no duplicate header. Verified.</li>
            <li><strong>Status:</strong> similar-items model is currently TRAINING. Slot renders nothing on live until model goes ACTIVE.</li>
          {%- else -%}
            <li>Unknown placement <code>{{ placement }}</code>. No decisions registered.</li>
        {%- endcase -%}
      </ul>
      <footer class="vrec-slot__notes-footer">
        These notes are visible on draft / preview themes only. They will not render on the live theme.
      </footer>
    </aside>
  {%- endif -%}

  <header class="vrec-slot__header">
    <h2 id="vrec-title-{{ placement }}" class="vrec-slot__title">{{ rec_title }}</h2>
    {%- if rec_subtitle != '' -%}
      <p class="vrec-slot__subtitle">{{ rec_subtitle }}</p>
    {%- endif -%}
  </header>

  <div class="vrec-slot__rail" role="list">
    {{ rail_html }}
  </div>
</section>

{%- endif -%}
